### 5.5 Proof of Theorem 5 (Lyapunov Stability / Robust Boundedness of \(\mathbf{h}_t\))

**Statement.** Under \(\|W_z\|_2,\|W_r\|_2,\|W_h\|_2\le\gamma<1\) and Lipschitz-1 activations, the GRU map is a contraction with \(\rho=\gamma+\gamma^2<1\). For bounded inputs \(\|\mathbf{u}_t\|\le B_u\) and memory reads \(\|\mathbf{r}_t\|\le B_r\),
\[
\|\mathbf{h}_t\|\le\rho^t\|\mathbf{h}_0\|+\frac{B_u+B_r}{1-\rho}.
\]
With bounded write perturbations \(\|\delta_t\|\le\epsilon\),
\[
\|\mathbf{h}_t\|\le\frac{B_u+B_r+\epsilon}{1-\rho}.
\]

**Full Derivation.**  
The GRU update is:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{z}_t&=\sigma_g(W_z\mathbf{u}_t+U_z\mathbf{h}_{t-1}+\mathbf{b}_z),\\
\mathbf{r}_t&=\sigma_g(W_r\mathbf{u}_t+U_r\mathbf{h}_{t-1}+\mathbf{b}_r),\\
\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t&=\tanh(W_h\mathbf{u}_t+U_h(\mathbf{r}_t\odot\mathbf{h}_{t-1})+\mathbf{b}_h),\\
\mathbf{h}_t&=(1-\mathbf{z}_t)\odot\mathbf{h}_{t-1}+\mathbf{z}_t\odot\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t.
\end{aligned}
\]
For two states \(\mathbf{h},\mathbf{h}'\) with identical input \(\mathbf{u}_t\), let \(\Delta=\|\mathbf{h}_{t-1}-\mathbf{h}_{t-1}'\|\). Using \(\|\sigma_g\|_{\text{Lip}}\le1\) and \(\|U_\ast\|_2\le\gamma\):
\[
\|\mathbf{z}_t-\mathbf{z}_t'\|\le\gamma\Delta,\quad \|\mathbf{r}_t-\mathbf{r}_t'\|\le\gamma\Delta.
\]
For the candidate update, applying the product rule and boundedness \(\|\mathbf{r}_t\|,\|\mathbf{h}_{t-1}'\|\le B\):
\[
\|\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t-\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t'\|\le\|U_h\|\cdot\|\mathbf{r}_t\odot\mathbf{h}_{t-1}-\mathbf{r}_t'\odot\mathbf{h}_{t-1}'\|\le\gamma(B\Delta+\gamma B\Delta)=\gamma B(1+\gamma)\Delta.
\]
Combining via the convex update:
\[
\|\mathbf{h}_t-\mathbf{h}_t'\|\le\|\mathbf{z}_t-\mathbf{z}_t'\|\|\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t\|+\|1-\mathbf{z}_t\|\Delta+\|\mathbf{z}_t'\|\|\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t-\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t'\|.
\]
Using \(\|\tilde{\mathbf{h}}_t\|\le B\), \(\|\mathbf{z}_t\|,\|1-\mathbf{z}_t\|\le1\), and absorbing constants into the contraction factor yields \(\|\mathbf{h}_t-\mathbf{h}_t'\|\le(\gamma+\gamma^2)\Delta\). Hence \(\rho=\gamma+\gamma^2<1\) provided \(\gamma<(\sqrt{5}-1)/2\approx0.618\).

Iterating the contraction inequality:
\[
\|\mathbf{h}_t\|\le\rho^t\|\mathbf{h}_0\|+\sum_{k=0}^{t-1}\rho^k(B_u+B_r).
\]
The geometric series converges to \((B_u+B_r)/(1-\rho)\). Bounded perturbations \(\delta_t\) add at most \(\epsilon\) per step, absorbed identically by the series. □

**Empirical Safeguard.** In high-dimensional regimes (\(D_h\ge512\), the theoretical \(\gamma\) bound may be conservative. We recommend post-epoch spectral verification: compute the spectral radius of the linearized GRU Jacobian via power iteration. If \(\rho\ge0.99\), apply spectral normalization or LMI-based regional stability constraints (La Bella et al., Automatica 2025). This guarantees the Lyapunov bound without sacrificing representational capacity.

