## Appendix B: World Model Variational Inference

### B.1 Standard VAE ELBO
**Theorem B.1.** For generative $p_\theta(x,z)$ and variational $q_\phi(z|x)$,
\[
\log p_\theta(x) = \mathcal{L}_{\text{ELBO}}(\theta,\phi) + \mathrm{KL}(q_\phi(z|x) \parallel p_\theta(z|x)) \geq \mathcal{L}_{\text{ELBO}}(\theta,\phi),
\]
where $\mathcal{L}_{\text{ELBO}} = \mathbb{E}_{q}[\log p_\theta(x|z)] - \mathrm{KL}(q_\phi(z|x) \parallel p(z))$.

*Proof.* Standard decomposition using $\log p(x) = \log \frac{p(x,z)}{p(z|x)}$ and non-negativity of KL. ∎

### B.2 RSSM Factorization and ELBO
**Definition B.1 (DreamerV3-style RSSM).** Latent trajectory $(\mathbf{h}_{1:T}, \mathbf{z}_{1:T})$ with:
- Deterministic: $\mathbf{h}_t = f_\phi(\mathbf{h}_{t-1}, \mathbf{z}_{t-1}, \mathbf{a}_{t-1})$
- Prior: $\hat{\mathbf{z}}_t \sim p_\phi(\mathbf{z}_t | \mathbf{h}_t)$
- Posterior: $\mathbf{z}_t \sim q_\phi(\mathbf{z}_t | \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{x}_t)$
- Decoders: $p_\phi(\mathbf{o}_t, r_t, c_t | \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t)$

**Theorem B.2 (Sequential ELBO).**
\[
\mathcal{L}_{\text{RSSM}} = \sum_{t=1}^T \mathbb{E}_{q}\left[\log p_\phi(\mathbf{o}_t, r_t, c_t | \mathbf{h}_t, \mathbf{z}_t)\right] - \sum_{t=1}^T \mathrm{KL}(q_\phi(\mathbf{z}_t|\mathbf{h}_t,\mathbf{x}_t) \parallel p_\phi(\mathbf{z}_t|\mathbf{h}_t)).
\]
*Proof.* Apply Thm B.1 to each timestep, exploit Markov factorization of $p$ and $q$, and sum. ∎

### B.3 Free-Bits Clipping
**Theorem B.3.** Define clipped loss $\mathcal{L}_{\text{clip}} = \sum_t \max(1, \mathrm{KL}(q\|p))$. Then $\mathcal{L}_{\text{clip}} \leq \log p(\cdot)$, preserving a valid (though looser) lower bound. Gradients w.r.t. encoder are zero when $\mathrm{KL} < 1$, preventing posterior collapse. ∎

### B.4 Reparameterization for Categorical Latents
DreamerV3 uses 32 independent categorical variables. We employ Gumbel-Softmax relaxation (Jang et al., 2017):
\[
\mathbf{z}_{t,k} = \text{softmax}\left(\frac{\log \boldsymbol{\pi}_{t,k} + \mathbf{g}}{\tau}\right), \quad \mathbf{g} \sim \text{Gumbel}(0,1).
\]
Gradients are biased for $\tau > 0$ but asymptotically unbiased as $\tau \to 0$. For analytical entropy bounds in Thm 2, we use a diagonal Gaussian approximation with KL error bounded by $\mathcal{O}(1/|\mathcal{Z}|)$.

