## Appendix C: Graph Neural Networks and Equivariance

### C.1 Message Passing Framework
**Definition C.1 (MPNN).** Layer $l$: $\mathbf{m}_{uv}^{(l)} = M^{(l)}(\mathbf{h}_u^{(l-1)}, \mathbf{h}_v^{(l-1)}, \mathbf{e}_{uv})$, $\mathbf{h}_v^{(l)} = U^{(l)}(\mathbf{h}_v^{(l-1)}, \sum_{u \in \mathcal{N}(v)} \mathbf{m}_{uv}^{(l)})$.

### C.2 $E(3)$-Equivariant Graph Neural Networks
**Theorem C.1 (EGNN Equivariance, Satorras et al., 2021).** Update:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{m}_{ij} &= \phi_e(\mathbf{h}_i, \mathbf{h}_j, \|\mathbf{x}_i - \mathbf{x}_j\|^2), \\
\mathbf{h}_i' &= \phi_h\left(\mathbf{h}_i, \sum_{j \neq i} \mathbf{m}_{ij}\right), \\
\mathbf{x}_i' &= \mathbf{x}_i + \sum_{j \neq i} (\mathbf{x}_i - \mathbf{x}_j) \phi_x(\mathbf{m}_{ij}).
\end{aligned}
\]
*Proof.* $\mathbf{m}_{ij}$ depends only on invariant distances/scalars. Coordinate update uses translation-invariant differences and scalar weights $\phi_x$, so $\mathbf{x}_i' \mapsto \mathbf{R}\mathbf{x}_i' + \mathbf{t}$ under $g=(\mathbf{R},\mathbf{t})$. Feature update uses invariant aggregation. ∎

### C.3 Discrete Symmetry and Conservation Bounds
**Theorem C.2 (Conservation Error under Approximate Equivariance).** Let $\tilde{\mathcal{G}}_{t+1}$ be the predicted graph. If trained with symmetry penalty $\mathcal{L}_{\text{sym}} = \mathbb{E}_g \|\hat{\mathbf{o}}_{t+1} - g^{-1}\cdot \hat{\mathbf{o}}_{t+1}(g\cdot\mathcal{G}_t)\|^2$, then
\[
\mathbb{E}\left[\left\|\sum_v m_v \Delta \mathbf{v}_v - \mathbf{F}_{\text{ext}}\Delta t\right\|\right] \leq C_1 \sqrt{\mathcal{L}_{\text{sym}}} + C_2 \Delta t^2 + \mathcal{O}(\epsilon_{\text{num}}).
\]
*Proof.* Taylor expand $\mathcal{L}_{\text{sym}}$ around identity. Infinitesimal generators of $E(3)$ correspond to linear/angular momentum. Discrete variational integrators (Marsden & West, 2001) show momentum drift scales with symmetry violation and timestep discretization. Finite precision adds $\epsilon_{\text{num}}$. ∎

