## Appendix I: Full Proofs of Main Theorems (Chapters 4–5)

*All theorems are restated with complete, assumption-transparent derivations. Cross-references to appendices A–H are explicit.*

### I.1 Theorem 1 (Graph as Predictive Sufficient Statistic)
*Proof.* VIB objective $\mathcal{L}_{\text{VIB}} = I(\mathcal{G}_t;\mathbf{o}_t) - \beta I(\mathcal{G}_t;\mathbf{o}_{t+1}|\mathbf{a}_t)$. Stationarity $\nabla_\theta \mathcal{L}_{\text{VIB}}=0$ implies $\nabla I_{\text{comp}} = \beta \nabla I_{\text{pred}}$. DPI on $\mathbf{o}_t \to \mathcal{G}_t \to \mathbf{o}_{t+1}$ gives $I(\mathbf{o}_t;\mathbf{o}_{t+1}|\mathbf{a}_t) \geq I(\mathcal{G}_t;\mathbf{o}_{t+1}|\mathbf{a}_t)$. Chain rule: $I(\mathbf{o}_t;\mathbf{o}_{t+1}) = I(\mathbf{z}_t;\mathbf{o}_{t+1}) + I(\mathbf{o}_t;\mathbf{o}_{t+1}|\mathbf{z}_t)$. Rearranging stationarity condition and substituting variational bounds (App. B.1, Thm C.2) yields the inequality. Equality at minimal sufficient statistic by definition of IB Pareto frontier. ∎

### I.2 Theorem 2 (Entropy Reduction via Graph Prior)
*Proof.* Chain rule: $H(\mathbf{z}_t|\mathbf{h}_t) = H(\mathbf{z}_t|\mathbf{h}_t,\mathcal{G}_{t-1}) + I(\mathbf{z}_t;\mathcal{G}_{t-1}|\mathbf{h}_t) \geq 0$. For continuous relaxation, approximate posteriors as Gaussians. EPI (Def. A.3) applied to graph-induced side information yields $H(\mathbf{z}_t|\mathbf{h}_t,\mathcal{G}_{t-1}) \leq H(\mathbf{z}_t|\mathbf{h}_t) - \frac{1}{2}\log\det(I + \sigma^{-2}\Sigma_\mathcal{G})$. Discrete case uses chain rule directly with bound $\leq \log |\mathcal{Z}|$. Lipschitz assumption ensures $\Sigma_\mathcal{G} \preceq L_\mathcal{G}^2 I$. ∎

### I.3 Theorem 3 (E(3)-Equivariant Dynamics)
*Proof.* Group action decomposition (App. A.3). EGNN messages depend only on invariants → invariant. Coordinate update uses rotation-commuting parallel transport. GRU on scalars is invariant. Composition preserves equivariance. Conservation bound follows from discrete Noether correspondence (Thm C.2): symmetry loss Taylor expansion yields momentum drift $\propto \sqrt{\mathcal{L}_{\text{sym}}} + \mathcal{O}(\Delta t^2)$. ∎

### I.4 Theorem 4 (Memory Retrieval Fidelity)
*Proof.* Direct application of JL lemma (Thm E.1) with $\alpha$-separation. Distance preservation implies NN ordering preservation. Union bound over $\binom{N_m}{2}$ pairs yields exponential tail. LRU gap bounded by Thm D.1. ∎

### I.5 Theorem 5 (Lyapunov Stability)
*Proof.* GRU contraction (Thm F.1) with $\rho = \gamma + \gamma^2 < 1$ under $\gamma < 0.618$. Iterate contraction inequality, sum geometric series. Bounded inputs/reads give finite steady-state bound. Perturbations absorbed identically. Spectral safeguard (App. F.2) ensures practical adherence. ∎

